result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracy L Wollin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Conceal (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tracy L Wollin in court with attorney Robert W. Flessas.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads no contest to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  State gives recommendations.  Attorney Flessas makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Parties request documents to be sealed.  Parties may file a motion.  
The Court Orders the Following: Count #1. 
FINE: $820.00
DNA Surcharge: Waived
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Total costs/fine/forfeiture: to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per month commencing 5/1/2016.  Failure to pay; the Court orders the defendant to serve 8 days in Huber
